  "2026-07-06T23:50:39.508Z",codex-agent,"Duplicate check: searched all statuses for context relevance scorer/plugin/weighting; no child item existed under pm-4k6b, only the broad parent and closed search relevance items."
  "2026-07-09T18:46:14.935Z",codex-root-20260709,"Implementation bundle: pm-h3no + pm-atfm + pm-lixy + pm-xmp5 share the context-ranking/evaluation write set. Duplicate-safe all-status orientation confirmed these are the canonical scorer, harness, corpus, and runner items; blocked index-store/packer items pm-3hps/pm-55ra remain out of scope until pm-801d/pm-dfg0 land."
  "2026-07-09T19:10:24.231Z",codex-root-20260709,"Progress evidence: public deterministic scorer, governed context_relevance override, shared context/next integration, opt-in per-signal explanations, corrected flag contracts, and SDK evaluation APIs are implemented. Focused tests, typecheck, ESLint, contract snapshot, and static/CodeFactor/token gates pass."
  "2026-07-09T19:50:41.842Z",codex-root-20260709,"Verification: fresh packed-artifact consumer installed @unbrained/pm-cli into an empty temp project and exercised defaultScoreContextCandidates, PmClient context/next ranking, runContextEvaluationCorpus, and installed CLI context --json --explain-ranking. Models and two-item CLI attribution were present; evaluation was 1.0 across all metrics. Full repo coverage passed 5,501 tests at 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-09T20:09:13.138Z",codex-root-20260709,"Pre-push Greptile 0460d109 feedback resolved: the provisional binary parent-presence graph signal weight was reduced from 0.45 to 0.15 so it cannot outweigh better-calibrated claim/recency signals before index-backed proximity lands. Golden evaluation remains 1.0 across all metrics."
  "2026-07-09T20:35:20.442Z",codex-root-20260709,"PR #487 Gemini round 1 addressed all scorer/runtime findings: sparse ContextResult/NextResult arrays now fall back safely, empty returned rankings score NDCG 0 when positive judgments exist, malformed runtime priorities default to no pressure, and invalid current timestamps yield zero deadline pressure. Full suite remains 5,501 tests at exact 100/100/100/100."
  "2026-07-09T20:53:09.045Z",codex-root-20260709,"PR #487 CodeRabbit/Greptile review: protected the structural baseline from runtime signal injection, removed the context-evaluation SDK module's reverse dependency on CLI command types via dedicated public read contracts, made pressure parsing tolerant and batch-parsed time once, and made the public SDK example project-relative. Hot-path verification confirmed active service lookup is an in-memory registry check with no file I/O. Full coverage remains exact 100%."
  "2026-07-09T21:07:15.375Z",codex-gpt5,"Review evidence: implemented Gemini's final metadata-shape hardening on the current PR head. Ranking now accepts deadline values supplied as ISO strings, Date objects, or epoch numbers; normalizes risk labels case-insensitively after trimming; and ignores non-string assignee values safely. Added focused runtime tests, including malformed extension metadata. Verification: focused context-relevance tests, typecheck, ESLint, static quality gate, and full sandboxed repository coverage all pass: 270 files, 5,502 tests, exact 100% statements (34,300/34,300), branches (24,511/24,511), functions (6,873/6,873), and lines (32,967/32,967)."
